content.text:
[
  {
    "span": "The outpost gates stay sealed until the Warden returns from the northern watch.",
    "issue": "Implies the Warden is alive and expected to return, which conflicts with the same guard's later claim that the Warden fell three nights ago (C-narrative-warden-status-consistency)."
  },
  {
    "span": "the Warden fell three nights ago. The elders simply haven't said so aloud yet.",
    "issue": "Directly contradicts the guard's own prior statement about the Warden returning, and the elder's statement that the Warden lives; also appears to reveal a concealed death the elders have not yet disclosed (C-narrative-warden-status-consistency, C-narrative-no-premature-spoiler)."
  },
  {
    "span": "The elders simply haven't said so aloud yet.",
    "issue": "May prematurely disclose withheld information (the Warden's death not yet announced) ahead of its intended reveal (C-narrative-no-premature-spoiler)."
  },
  {
    "span": "The Warden lives and is in good health; she will address the outpost herself at dusk.",
    "issue": "Contradicts the guard's claim that the Warden fell three nights ago; warden status is inconsistent across speakers (C-narrative-warden-status-consistency)."
  },
  {
    "span": "Commander Vale, of course. She's led it since the siege, three winters back.",
    "issue": "Conflicts with the earlier premise that the Warden holds/leads the garrison; unclear who commands the outpost (C-narrative-warden-status-consistency)."
  }
]

